---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Editorial Policy"
  description="How Korea Travel Guide is made: our sources, our use of AI assistance, and our commitment to accurate, licensed content."
>
  <div class="page-hero">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="eyebrow">Editorial policy</p>
      <h1>How this site is made</h1>
    </div>
  </div>
  <article class="article wrap">
    <div class="prose">
    <p>
      Korea Travel Guide is a curated, editor-reviewed resource for
      international visitors. We're transparent about how it's produced.
    </p>

    <h2>AI assistance</h2>
    <p>
      Our guides are drafted with AI assistance and then checked against live
      data. We disclose this on every article. AI helps us keep coverage broad
      and up to date; it does not replace factual verification.
    </p>

    <h2>Where our facts come from</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Business details, ratings, and hours: Google Places data.</li>
      <li>Practical info (visa, emergency, transport): official government and tourism sources.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Our verification standards</h2>
    <p>
      Because coverage is broad, we hold every venue guide to concrete,
      automated standards rather than opinions:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Quality floor:</strong> when verified rating data is available, we only feature places rated 4.0★ or higher with a meaningful number of reviews.</li>
      <li><strong>Freshness:</strong> venue data is re-checked on a schedule; anything that has closed is automatically unpublished, so we don't send you to a place that no longer exists.</li>
      <li><strong>Licensed images only:</strong> every image comes from an approved, licensed source (Google Places, Unsplash, or public/open data) with attribution — never a scraped photo.</li>
      <li><strong>No invented details:</strong> our drafting process is explicitly instructed never to fabricate hours, prices, or addresses; specifics come from data, not guesswork.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Guides are produced by the Korea Travel Guide editorial team using this
      process. We do not claim personal visits we haven't made — we're a
      curation-and-verification resource, and we say so.
    </p>

    <h2>Images</h2>
    <p>
      We only use images we are licensed to use — official Places photos,
      public-domain and openly-licensed sources (e.g. Korea Tourism Organization
      open data, Unsplash), or images we credit and link to their source. We do
      not republish others' photos without a license.
    </p>

    <h2>Corrections</h2>
    <p>
      Found something out of date? Places close and prices change. We update
      automatically, but if you spot an error, let us know.
    </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
